ISE Basic CLI Commands

# sign == executive mode 
# (terminal) == configuration mode
config terminal == configuration mode

--executive mode commands--
cls / ctrl+l == clear screen
application start = start an application
show application status ise == show all apps running
application stop = stop an application
? == help same like cisco routers and switches
set clock H:M:S:YYYY = set date and time
copy running-config startup-config == save
copy startup-config running-config == restore
show running-config == show all the configuration details
debug ? /debug all == show logs for debugging
undebug all == exit debugging mode 
reload == reboot
halt == shutdown
password == change password 
ping == ping 
traceroute == check routes to ip/domain
ssh == connect ssh to other machine
show interface g0 == shows info about interface and IP. 
show ip route == check all routes
show backup statu == shows backup 
show cdp neigbour == shows neighbours for cdp
show clock == clock
show uptime == shows how much time is working
shows users == shows number of users logged in 
show version == current v

-- configuration mode --
config terminal == terminal access
interface xx == gets into the interface
ip address xx xx == changes the ip address of the int. 
no shut == up the port. 
ip default-gateway xxxxx == set default gateway. 
username xxxx password xxxx role admin/user == to create new user and assign role. 





