-- Checking and Assigning Personas --

We have 4 personas (Administration, Monitoring, Policy Services, pxGrid)

1. PAN (policy Administration Node) responsible for managing policy and configurations.
2. MnT (Monitoring) resposible for monitoring 
3. PSN (Policy Service Node) resposible for enforcing policies and providing network access. 

-- We can assign px grid from personas 

-- Roles --

We have three types of roles
1. Primary
2. Secondary
3. Standalone

We can make administration or monitoring as primary or secondary roles. PSNs never get primary or secondary. 

-- Identities --

Identitites are ways to identify the users, whether it could be MAC, email, LDAP, SAML, CS, Internal & External connectors for identity. 
Identity database stores the credentials to authenticate. 

